Senate President Abubakar Saraki has paid N16.9 million salary arrears to workers of Irepodun Local Government Area of Kwara State, the chairman of the council, Muyiwa Oladipo, said yesterday. He said this was in fulfilment of Saraki’s pledge to help settle salary arrears owed workers of  some local government areas in the state . Oladipo said the gesture would alleviate the challenges faced by workers. He said this was another evidence of Saraki’s commitment to alleviating the plight of local government workers. Saraki releases N16.9m for LG salary arrears Saraki promises to offset Kwara workers salary arrears Saraki pledges to clear Kwara workers’ salary arrears